<BaseLayout title="Weapon Balancing" description="Detailed breakdown of weapon damage balancing across all TAOM cultures">
  <div class="page-content mod-info">
    <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/mod-info">Mod Info</a> / Weapon Balancing</nav>
    <h1 class="page-title">Weapon Balancing</h1>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        TAOM includes <strong>300 custom melee weapons</strong> across <strong>13 cultures</strong> (with 3 more planned).
        Unlike armour and troop skills, weapons are individually designed — each has unique blade weight, damage factors
        and crafting pieces. This analysis computes <strong>estimated damage</strong> using the full TaleWorlds physics simulation
        to assess balance across cultures.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Gondor is the baseline (100%). Cultures above 130% may have weapons that are too powerful relative to their
        lore position. Cultures below 70% likely have placeholder or incomplete weapon data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>The Formula</h2>
      <div class="formula-box">
        <code>Damage = f(blade weight, damage factor, swing speed, weapon reach, impact point)</code>
      </div>
      <div class="formula-details">
        <div class="detail-card">
          <h3>Full Physics Simulation</h3>
          <p>Damage values are computed using the full TaleWorlds physics model extracted from decompiled game code, including rotational momentum, impact point calculations, and speed modifiers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card">
          <h3>Blade Weight &amp; Damage Factor</h3>
          <p>From the weapon's blade crafting piece. Heavier blades and higher damage factors produce more kinetic energy transfer on impact.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card">
          <h3>Swing vs Thrust</h3>
          <p>Swing damage uses rotational momentum (higher potential). Thrust damage uses linear momentum (lower but more consistent). Both are computed separately per weapon.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card">
          <h3>Average Melee</h3>
          <p>Each weapon's "melee damage" is its average across swing and thrust values. Culture averages are the mean across all weapons in that culture's arsenal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Quick Comparison</h2>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table class="comparison-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Culture</th>
              <th class="skill-col">Melee</th>
              <th class="skill-col">Ranged</th>
              <th class="skill-col">Avg Melee</th>
              <th class="skill-col">Avg Ranged</th>
              <th class="skill-col">Melee %</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {cultures.map(c => {
              const pctNum = parseInt(c.meleePercent);
              const pctCls = isNaN(pctNum) ? 'mod-zero' : pctNum > 130 ? 'mod-warn' : pctNum > 110 ? 'mod-pos' : pctNum < 70 ? 'mod-crit' : pctNum < 90 ? 'mod-neg' : 'mod-zero';
              return (
                <tr>
                  <td class="culture-cell" style={`background: ${c.color}22; border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}><a href={`#${c.id}`}>{c.name}</a></td>
                  <td class="center culture-cell" style={`background: ${c.color}15`}>{c.meleeWeapons || '—'}</td>
                  <td class="center culture-cell" style={`background: ${c.color}15`}>{c.rangedWeapons || '—'}</td>
                  <td class="center">{c.avgMelee || '—'}</td>
                  <td class="center">{c.avgRanged || '—'}</td>
                  <td class={`center ${pctCls}`}>{c.meleePercent}</td>
                </tr>
              );
            })}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="table-legend">
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot mod-pos-bg"></span> 110-130% — Above average</span>
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot mod-warn-bg"></span> &gt;130% — Potentially overpowered</span>
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot mod-neg-bg"></span> 70-90% — Below average</span>
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot mod-crit-bg"></span> &lt;70% — Potentially underpowered</span>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Balance Concerns</h2>
      <div class="concerns-list">
        {balanceConcerns.map(concern => (
          <div class={`concern-item concern-${concern.severity}`}>
            <div class="concern-header">
              <span class={`concern-badge concern-badge-${concern.severity}`}>{concern.severity}</span>
              <strong>{concern.culture}</strong>
            </div>
            <p class="concern-issue">{concern.issue}</p>
            <p class="concern-rec">{concern.recommendation}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Culture Details</h2>

      {cultures.map(c => (
        <div id={c.id} class="culture-card" style={`background: ${c.color}1a; border: 1px solid ${c.color}40; border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}>
          <div class="culture-header">
            <h3 style={`color: ${c.color}`}>{c.name}</h3>
            <div class="culture-meta">
              <span class="culture-badge" style={`background: ${c.color}25; color: ${c.color}`}>{c.alignment === 'good' ? 'Free Peoples' : c.alignment === 'neutral' ? 'Neutral Kingdom' : 'Forces of Darkness'}</span>
              <span class="culture-badge" style={`background: ${c.color}20; color: ${c.color}cc`}>{c.race}</span>
              {(c.meleeWeapons + c.rangedWeapons) > 0 && <span class="culture-badge" style={`background: ${c.color}20; color: ${c.color}cc`}>{c.meleeWeapons + c.rangedWeapons} weapons</span>}
              {c.meleePercent !== '—' && <span class="culture-badge" style={`background: ${c.color}20; color: ${c.color}cc`}>{c.meleePercent} melee</span>}
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="culture-identity">{c.identity}</p>

          {c.primaryWeapons.length > 0 && (
            <div class="culture-weapons">
              <strong>Primary Weapons:</strong> {c.primaryWeapons.join(' · ')}
            </div>
          )}

          <div class="modifiers-grid">
            {c.strengths.length > 0 && (
              <div class="mod-section strengths">
                <h4>Strengths</h4>
                <ul>
                  {c.strengths.map(s => (
                    <li>
                      <span class="mod-skill">{s.stat}</span>
                      <span class="mod-value pos">{s.mod}</span>
                      <span class="mod-note">{s.note}</span>
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            )}

            {c.weaknesses.length > 0 && (
              <div class="mod-section weaknesses">
                <h4>Weaknesses</h4>
                <ul>
                  {c.weaknesses.map(w => (
                    <li>
                      <span class="mod-skill">{w.stat}</span>
                      <span class="mod-value neg">{w.mod}</span>
                      <span class="mod-note">{w.note}</span>
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            )}
          </div>

          {c.notes && <p class="culture-notes">{c.notes}</p>}
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Weapon Class Averages</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Cross-culture average estimated damage per weapon class. These represent the global baseline for each weapon type.
      </p>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table class="baseline-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Weapon Class</th>
              <th>Avg Swing</th>
              <th>Avg Thrust</th>
              <th>Cultures</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {weaponClassAverages.map(wc => (
              <tr>
                <td>{wc.weaponClass}</td>
                <td>{wc.avgSwing || '—'}</td>
                <td>{wc.avgThrust || '—'}</td>
                <td>{wc.cultures}</td>
                <td class="note-cell">{wc.note}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Damage Distribution</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Expected damage hierarchy based on weapon physics. Two-handed weapons should deal roughly 1.5-2x the damage of their one-handed counterparts due to higher blade weight and longer swing arcs.
      </p>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table class="baseline-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Tier</th><th>Weapon Types</th><th>Expected Range</th><th>Current Avg</th><th>Status</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Tier 1 — Light</td><td>1H Swords, 1H Axes</td><td>50-90</td><td>62-69</td><td class="status-ok">OK</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tier 2 — Medium</td><td>2H Swords, Polearms</td><td>70-110</td><td>52-102</td><td class="status-low">Low (polearms)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tier 3 — Heavy</td><td>2H Axes, Maces</td><td>90-140</td><td>71-120</td><td class="status-ok">OK</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tier 4 — Crushing</td><td>2H Maces</td><td>100-160</td><td>118</td><td class="status-ok">OK</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Thrust-Focused</td><td>Pikes</td><td>40-70</td><td>40/55 swing/thrust</td><td class="status-ok">OK</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

